text: Kamen-Rybolov () is a rural locality (a selo) and the administrative center of Khankaysky District of Primorsky Krai, Russia, located on the shores of Lake Khanka. Population: ==History== It was founded by peasants who migrated from the western regions of Russia (modern day Belarus) and by the Cossacks in 1865. ==References== ===Notes=== ===Sources=== * * Category:Rural localities in Primorsky Krai
